[0m[33;1m[1;3mcommit b50eba22735bbfab7a510a55979e7f367fd3e752
Author: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
Date:   Fri Jun 6 13:52:01 2025 +0200

    Use indexUUID as an index identifier instead of the indexName
    
    In order to support metadata only modifications like table name
    renames, indices must be purly addressed by their indexUUID,
    especially at the shard routing to avoid any shard allocation
    re-processing.
    Relation name handling should be only based on the recently added
    RelationMetadata entities.
    
    The `indexName` property is still written to the IndexMetadata
    for backward compatibility, mainly to read and upgrade older indices.
    It's marked as deprecated and should be fully removed in future.
    
    Relates to #17518, #17075.

